Package: mixturemodelsr
Type: Package
Title: R Wrapper for the Mixture-Models Python Library
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Siva Rajesh", "Kasa", email = "sivarajesh.kasa@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Provides an R interface to the 'Mixture-Models' Python package 
    (Kasa & Rajan, 2020) via reticulate. Supports fitting Gaussian Mixture Models (GMM),
    Mixture of Factor Analyzers (MFA), Parsimonious GMM (PGMM), MCLUST family,
    and t-mixture models using gradient-based optimization including Newton-CG.
    The Python library uses automatic differentiation for efficient parameter estimation.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
